<seg id="33">For example, in Prague will act Chinaski, Support lesbiens, Illustratosphere with Dan Bárta, The Tap Tap, Marián Bango and Jiří Suchý.</seg>
<seg id="34">For more detailed information, you can consult www.kpks.cz.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="35">Do you have scheduled another "spectacular" similar action in the future?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="36">In May, we will act for the first time in the festival Pražské bird, so here surely we will prepare a program attractive with interesting guests.</seg>
<seg id="37">Next year we would also like to play at the Bohemian National Hall in New York and me, personally, taking advantage of that we are in the United States, I would like to complete it with performances in Washington and in Chicago.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="38">Your plans abroad are not precisely minimalist, until now have done for example in Madrid, Brussels, London, or Moscow.</seg>
<seg id="39">The Tap Tap is, however, a group formed by people with disabilities.</seg>
<seg id="40">How is the logistics and organization of these trips?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="41">It is not so difficult to how it might seem at first glance.</seg>
<seg id="42">There are five members in electric wheelchair, chairs must travel in the luggage compartment and in addition we carry much weight, the boxes with the instruments...</seg>
<seg id="43">However, until now we have managed well. ČSA and British Airways were well prepared, which never ceases to amaze me.</seg>
<seg id="44">Even in Moscow, where we have returned recently, went all without problems.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="45">Thanks to the exits abroad can compare the different society's attitudes towards the disabled and other aspects.</seg>
<seg id="46">What you have found so far?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="47">In Madrid, Luxembourg, London and other cities, everything works better than here; in Russia, we have seen that, in the east, there is still a long way to go.</seg>
<seg id="48">Unlike in Prague, Moscow is full of barriers, there is still not common for a person moves alone for the city centre in an electric wheelchair.</seg>
<seg id="49">Something as ordinary as it is, for example, give preference to someone in a wheelchair in the elevator, there is not.</seg>
<seg id="50">Fortunately, it has created a civil partnership that strives to focus attention to the problems of people with disabilities.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="51">In what ways we must follow the example of more advanced countries?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="52">There are many ways in which we are going behind...</seg>
<seg id="53">But it is important to mention that the improvement and the improvement of the situation always depends on the people it affects directly.</seg>
<seg id="54">In London and Madrid is quite normal for people with a severe disability travel on their own in public and can go to the service, to the museum, where you go.</seg>
<seg id="55">But it is not very common for a large number of people with disabilities to participate in social life actively, in this respect, with The Tap Tap let go a little bit ahead!</seg>
