</p>
<p>
<seg id="63">It is true that helped us a lot to connect with famous singers and also work actively to promote the group.</seg>
<seg id="64">We came to the conclusion that the work that is not seen, it is as if it did not exist.</seg>
<seg id="65">Thanks to the aid from the European Union, we can afford to also quality teachers, equipment, etc.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="66">Do you had intended to go as far with The Tap Tap?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="67">From the beginning I saw the potential that he had, that something can be done differently.</seg>
<seg id="68">The entertainment world is full of things that seem to each other.</seg>
<seg id="69">It is logical, in their own way, everything new is viewed with caution and takes a long time to be accepted.</seg>
<seg id="70">There are few extraordinary things, but I dare say that The Tap Tap is one of them.</seg>
<seg id="71">The impression of someone who sees us for the first time is clearly compassion, is a natural reaction...</seg>
<seg id="72">But compassion is totally superfluous because people with disabilities are not abandoned beings that suffer and that we should have compassion.</seg>
<seg id="73">There are people who are able to live a full life and develop, on condition, of course, that has the necessary means.</seg>
<seg id="74">I always say that if something goes well for them to people with disabilities, then, is not only a breakthrough for them, but for society as a whole.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="75">How Assisted the fact that you are a demanding boss, as he describes many people?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="76">If we want to do a good job, we have to be rigorous in many respects and require some discipline.</seg>
<seg id="77">I think it is completely normal.</seg>
<seg id="78">Some people come with a romantic vision and with their heads in the clouds and when they learn that they have to go two days to rehearse, go to the preparatory test and spend a lot of time traveling and concerts, the initial euphoria quickly abandons them.</seg>
<seg id="79">But that is how it works everywhere, in every group that wants to work and achieve something.</seg>
</p>
<p>
